OL,3,C'It is the saddest thing':
OL,4,CMisinterpreted ECG tests result in
OL,5,Cfatal consequences
OL,7,FHer mother has spoken of the
OL,8,Fdevastation of finding out that her
OL,9,FECG test results had been
OL,10,Fmisinterpreted at the time, saying:
OL,11,F"It is the saddest thing in the whole
OL,12,Ftragedy that we've been through, to
OL,13,Fknow that her death could have been
OL,14,Fprevented if that ECG from the year
OL,15,Fbefore had been interpreted correctly".
OL,17,FITV News has been made aware of quite
OL,18,Fa few cases where patients have been
OL,19,Fdischarged after having ECGs, before
OL,20,Fdying from heart conditions which were
OL,21,Fevident in their test results.
