OL,3,C'It is the saddest thing':
OL,4,CMisinterpreted ECG tests result in
OL,5,Cfatal consequences
OL,7,F"If your child has gone to A&E and is
OL,8,Fhaving an ECG, you want to know that
OL,9,Fthe person reading it is a specialist,
OL,10,Fknows exactly what they're looking for.
OL,12,F"So it's really important that these
OL,13,Fchanges are made where young people's
OL,14,FECGs and, in fact, all people's ECGs
OL,15,Fare read by those specialists."
OL,17,FThat is a sentiment shared by
OL,18,Fcampaigner Sally Bee who told us about
OL,19,Fher experience as a patient with a
OL,20,Frare heart condition.
