OL,3,C'It is the saddest thing':
OL,4,CMisinterpreted ECG tests result in
OL,5,Cfatal consequences
OL,7,F"I've now survived six heart attacks
OL,8,Fand that has been many visits to
OL,9,Fhospital as you can imagine" she said.
OL,11,F"I can remember three examples where I
OL,12,Fknow the ECGs have not been
OL,13,Funderstood...That shouldn't happen,
OL,14,Fthat doctor should have been taught
OL,15,Fhow to read the ECG, but, if that
OL,16,Fdoctor is unsure, then it should go
OL,17,Fstraight to a cardiologist and that's
OL,18,Fwhat hasn't happened on any of those
OL,19,Foccasions."
