OL,3,C'It is the saddest thing':
OL,4,CMisinterpreted ECG tests result in
OL,5,Cfatal consequences
OL,7,F"NHS trusts are responsible for
OL,8,Fensuring their staff follow the latest
OL,9,Fclinical guidance."
OL,11,FIt is hoped the interpretation of ECGs
OL,12,Fcould be improved with the development
OL,13,Fof artificial intelligence. This is
OL,14,Fcurrently being looked into at the
OL,15,FSchool of Medical Sciences at City St
OL,16,FGeorge's, University of London.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
