OL,3,C'It is the saddest thing':
OL,4,CMisinterpreted ECG tests result in
OL,5,Cfatal consequences
OL,7,F"Obviously, that will save time, it
OL,8,Fcould potentially save money and very,
OL,9,Fvery importantly... it can save from
OL,10,Fpotential mistakes."
OL,12,FFor the family of Clarissa, it can't
OL,13,Fcome soon enough. For now though,
OL,14,Fthey're calling for all ECGs to be
OL,15,Flooked at by specialists.
OL,17,FOtherwise, they say, that opportunity
OL,18,Fto save lives will keep being missed.
OL,20,FFor more information and support, you
OL,21,Fcan contact Cardiac Risk in the Young
